{
  "page": "King's justice (concept)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>king's justice</b> is a legal concept of royal <a href=\"/index.php/Justice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Justice\">justice</a> devised by <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Andals,_the_Rhoynar_and_the_First_Men\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King of the Andals, the Rhoynar and the First Men\">King</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> for the subjects of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>. It is related to the concept of the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_peace\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King&#39;s peace\">king's peace</a>, as those who break it are expected to face the king's justice, usually in the form of execution.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> As such, the term gives its name to the title held by the royal executioner, the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Justice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King&#39;s Justice\">King's Justice</a>.\n</p><p>The concept was kept under the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"House Baratheon of King&#39;s Landing\">Baratheon</a> dynasty.\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> has the authority to sit the Iron Throne to dispense the king's justice whenever the king is absent, sick, or indisposed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The lords of the constituent regions of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> have the authority to dispense the king's justice within their regions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_justice_(concept)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a> made the journey to <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a> to bring the king's justice to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a> for selling poachers into <a href=\"/index.php/Slavery\" title=\"Slavery\">slavery</a>, but Mormont had already fled beyond his reach.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot2.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_events\">Recent events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_justice_(concept)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_justice_(concept)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> is considered old enough to join <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Snow\" title=\"Jon Snow\">his</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">brothers</a> and witness <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">his father</a> enforcing the king's justice: the execution of a <a href=\"/index.php/Night%27s_Watch\" title=\"Night&#39;s Watch\">Night's Watch</a> deserter, <a href=\"/index.php/Gared\" title=\"Gared\">Gared</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a> counsels Lord Eddard to accept the title of Hand of the King, as it would grant him the power to investigate the truth about the death of <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Arryn\" title=\"Jon Arryn\">Jon Arryn</a>, and bring his killers to the king's justice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> bids <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">her father</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Bannermen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bannermen\">bannermen</a> to arrest <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> for the attempted murder of her son, <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a>, and help her take him to <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> to await the king's justice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot28.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a>, Tyrion Lannister questions how the king's justice is carried out in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vale\">Vale</a> after being thrown into the <a href=\"/index.php/Sky_cells\" title=\"Sky cells\">sky cells</a> for defending his innocence and denying the crimes of which <a href=\"/index.php/Lysa_Arryn\" title=\"Lysa Arryn\">Lysa Arryn</a>&#160;and <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a>&#160;accuse him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Later, when <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Arryn\" title=\"Robert Arryn\">Robert Arryn</a> calls for Tyrion to fly out the <a href=\"/index.php/Moon_Door\" title=\"Moon Door\">Moon Door</a>, Lysa has the door opened to intimidate the prisoner, calling it \"the king's justice\". In response, Tyrion publicly demands <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> calls out Eddard for Tyrion's arrest, he reminds her that as Hand of the King, he has been charged by her <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">husband</a> to keep the king's peace and enforce the king's justice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> is accused of carrying out <a href=\"/index.php?title=Gregor_Clegane%27s_raid_on_the_riverlands&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Gregor Clegane&#39;s raid on the riverlands (page does not exist)\">raids</a> on the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">Riverlands</a> and slaughtering the smallfolk of <a href=\"/index.php/Sherrer\" title=\"Sherrer\">Sherrer</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Wendish_Town\" title=\"Wendish Town\">Wendish Town</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Mummer%27s_Ford\" title=\"Mummer&#39;s Ford\">Mummer's Ford</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Grand_Maester\" title=\"Grand Maester\">Grand Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Pycelle\" title=\"Pycelle\">Pycelle</a> disagrees that the accusations are the concern of the throne, and argues that the accusers should seek justice from Ser Gregor's liege lord, <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>. Lord Stark counters that the king's justice is the concern of the entire realm, in the king's name regardless of the location. Pycelle then counsels to wait for Robert's return, but Lord Stark cuts him short, reminding him that he speaks with the King's voice. Afterward, as Eddard is unable to carry out his sentence personally due to his injuries, he charges Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Beric_Dondarrion\" title=\"Beric Dondarrion\">Beric Dondarrion</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Thoros_of_Myr\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thoros of Myr\">Thoros of Myr</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gladden_Wylde\" title=\"Gladden Wylde\">Gladden Wylde</a>, and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lothar_Mallery\" title=\"Lothar Mallery\">Lothar Mallery</a> to bring the king's justice to Ser Gregor and those that joined him in his crimes. Eddard sentences Ser Gregor to <a href=\"/index.php/Attainder\" title=\"Attainder\">attainder</a> and execution.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Later on, when Pycelle warns Ned that Tywin is wroth about the force sent to execute Ser Gregor, Ned counters that Tywin may write all the letters he wants to the Queen, but should he interfere with the king's justice, he will have to answer to Robert.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_justice_(concept)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>While stranded on the <a href=\"/index.php/Spears_of_the_merling_king\" title=\"Spears of the merling king\">spears of the merling king</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a> spies a <a href=\"/index.php/Shayala%27s_Dance\" title=\"Shayala&#39;s Dance\">ship</a>. He reaches for the pouch containing his fingerbones, but finds nothing. Recalling <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a> asking him why he had kept the bones, Davos whispers that he keeps them to remind himself of Stannis' justice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After reuniting with <a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Harwin\" title=\"Harwin\">Harwin</a> tells her that he heard Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Beric_Dondarrion\" title=\"Beric Dondarrion\">Beric Dondarrion</a> state that the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">war</a> began when the Hand of the King sent Beric to bring the king's justice to Ser Gregor, and that he means to carry out the task.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prior to their <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a>, Beric Dondarrion tells <a href=\"/index.php/Sandor_Clegane\" title=\"Sandor Clegane\">Sandor Clegane</a> that the <a href=\"/index.php/Brotherhood_without_banners\" title=\"Brotherhood without banners\">brotherhood without banners</a> was born from the six score men sent out to bring the king's justice to Sandor's brother.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_justice_(concept)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>In the name of <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">Robert</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Baratheon\" title=\"House Baratheon\">House Baratheon</a>, the First of his Name, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Andals_and_the_Rhoynar_and_the_First_Men\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King of the Andals and the Rhoynar and the First Men\">King of the Andals and the Rhoynar and the First Men</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Lord of the Seven Kingdoms\">Lord of the Seven Kingdoms</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Protector_of_the_Realm\" title=\"Protector of the Realm\">Protector of the Realm</a>, by the word of <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">House Stark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Lord of Winterfell\">Lord of Winterfell</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Warden_of_the_North\" title=\"Warden of the North\">Warden of the North</a>, I do sentence you to die.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Gared\" title=\"Gared\">Gared</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>All <a href=\"/index.php/Justice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Justice\">justice</a> flows from the king.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Cersei:</b> By what right do you dare lay hands on <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">my blood</a>? Who do you think you are?<br />\n<b>Eddard:</b> The <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>. Charged by <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">your own lord husband</a> to keep the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_peace\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"King&#39;s peace\">king's peace</a> and enforce the king's justice.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot39.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Pycelle:</b> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Gregor_Clegane%27s_raid_on_the_riverlands&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Gregor Clegane&#39;s raid on the riverlands (page does not exist)\">These crimes</a> are no concern of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">throne</a>. Let them seek Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin's</a> justice.<br />\n<b>Eddard:</b> It is all the king's justice. North, south, east, or west, all we do we do in <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">Robert's</a> name.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Pycelle\" title=\"Pycelle\">Pycelle</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I've heard <a href=\"/index.php/Beric_Dondarrion\" title=\"Beric Dondarrion\">his lordship</a> say <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Five_Kings\" title=\"War of the Five Kings\">this war</a> began when <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">the Hand</a> sent him out to bring the king's justice to <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a>, and that's how he means for it to end.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Harwin\" title=\"Harwin\">Harwin</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Daenerys:</b> Why do the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a> make kings and queens, if not to protect the ones who can't protect themselves?<br />\n</p><p><b>Jorah:</b> Some kings make themselves. <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Baratheon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Baratheon\">Robert</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Robert%27s_Rebellion\" title=\"Robert&#39;s Rebellion\">did</a>.<br />\n</p>\n<b>Daenerys:</b> He was no true king. He did no <a href=\"/index.php/Justice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Justice\">justice</a>. Justice... that's what kings are for.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=King%27s_justice_(concept)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_r